+# Proposal: types-and-helpers
+
+> Phase ph.2-core-engine — types extension, coordKey helper, and winCheck with TDD coverage.
+
+---
+
+## Intent
+
+Establish the type foundation and the first pure-logic module (`winCheck`) for the game core. Without these, `move.ts`, `history.ts`, and `reducer.ts` (changes c2 and c3) cannot be implemented.
+
+1. **What problem**: After ph.1, `src/types.ts` has `Direction`, `Coord`, `Tile`, `Intent` — but the reducer needs `Level`, `GameState`, `HistoryEntry`, `AnimSpec`. The `winCheck` algorithm needs a `coordKey` helper because `Set<Coord>` uses object identity and our reducer produces fresh `Coord` objects.
+2. **Who is affected**: c2 (move + history) and c3 (reducer) — both depend on the types and the coordKey helper. ph.3's level loader consumes `Level`.
+3. **If we don't make this change**: c2 and c3 cannot proceed.
+4. **Type**: prerequisite / foundation.
+5. **Linkage**: required by c2, c3, and ph.3 (first level).
+
+---
+
+## Scope
+
+### In scope
+
+- Extend `src/types.ts` with:
+  - `Level` interface (grid dimensions, walls, targets, player start, box starts)
+  - `GameState` interface (immutable per D3; includes `initial` ref for reset per research finding)
+  - `HistoryEntry` interface (entry-based per D5)
+  - `AnimSpec` interface (per D8)
+- Add `src/core/coordKey.ts` — pure helper `coordKey(c: Coord): string` returning `"x,y"`
+- Add `src/core/winCheck.ts` — `winCheck(state: GameState): boolean` (per D4)
+- Add `src/core/createInitialState.ts` — factory `createInitialState(level: Level): GameState`
+- Tests under `tests/unit/core/`:
+  - `coordKey.test.ts` — basic coordKey behavior (4 tests)
+  - `winCheck.test.ts` — win detection (4 tests covering no-boxes, all-on-targets, partial, empty)
+  - `createInitialState.test.ts` — initial state from Level (3 tests)
+
+### Out of scope
+
+- `move.ts` — c2
+- `history.ts` — c2
+- `reducer.ts` — c3
+- Any DOM-touching code — ph.3+
+- Level JSON loader — ph.3
+- Renderer / gameShell — ph.3
+- Animator — ph.5
+
+---
+
+## Approach
+
+Pure types + pure helpers. Zero side effects.
+
+**`src/types.ts` extensions** (additions, not replacements):
+- `Level` — shape of one level: dimensions, walls Set, targets Set, player start, box starts
+- `GameState` — runtime state: levelId, static (Level shared by ref), player, boxes, moveCount, history, won, initial (for reset)
+- `HistoryEntry` — single entry in undo stack
+- `AnimSpec` — animation request: from, to, duration, entities (player + pushed box index)
+
+**`src/core/coordKey.ts`**:
+```ts
+export function coordKey(c: Coord): string {
+  return `${c.x},${c.y}`;
+}
+```
+
+**`src/core/winCheck.ts`**:
+```ts
+export function winCheck(state: GameState): boolean {
+  if (state.boxes.length !== state.static.targets.size) return false;
+  const targetKeys = new Set(Array.from(state.static.targets).map(coordKey));
+  return state.boxes.every((b) => targetKeys.has(coordKey(b)));
+}
+```
+
+**`src/core/createInitialState.ts`**:
+```ts
+export function createInitialState(level: Level, levelId: string): GameState {
+  return {
+    levelId,
+    static: level,
+    player: { ...level.playerStart },
+    boxes: level.boxStarts.map((c) => ({ ...c })),
+    moveCount: 0,
+    history: [],
+    won: false,
+    initial: { player: { ...level.playerStart }, boxes: level.boxStarts.map((c) => ({ ...c })) },
+  };
+}
+```
+
+**Tests**: each test sets up a small Level inline (no JSON loader yet). Uses Vitest's `describe`/`it`/`expect` per D10.
+
+---
+
+## Must-haves
+
+1. MUST export from `src/types.ts`: `Level`, `GameState`, `HistoryEntry`, `AnimSpec` (in addition to existing `Direction`, `Coord`, `Tile`, `Intent`).
+2. MUST export `coordKey(c: Coord): string` from `src/core/coordKey.ts`.
+3. MUST export `winCheck(state: GameState): boolean` from `src/core/winCheck.ts` returning true only when every box is on a target tile.
+4. MUST export `createInitialState(level: Level, levelId: string): GameState` from `src/core/createInitialState.ts` with `won: false`, `moveCount: 0`, `history: []`, and an `initial` field capturing the starting positions.
+5. MUST have ≥ 11 passing unit tests across `coordKey.test.ts`, `winCheck.test.ts`, and `createInitialState.test.ts`.
+6. MUST NOT introduce any DOM imports in `src/core/` (verifiable by `grep`).
+7. MUST keep `npm run build` and `npx tsc --noEmit` passing.
+
+---
+
+## Non-goals
+
+- Not implementing move validation logic (c2).
+- Not implementing history push/pop (c2).
+- Not implementing the reducer orchestrator (c3).
+- Not implementing level loading from JSON (ph.3).
+- Not implementing deadlock detection (ph.8).
+- Not adding lint / commit hooks (ph.9).
+- Not changing test infrastructure (already verified by ph.1 c4).
\ No newline at end of file
