+# Context: ph.2-core-engine
+
+> Phase: ph.2-core-engine  |  Milestone: M1-core-playable  |  Mode: mvp
+> Goal: Implement and unit-test the pure game rules in `src/core/`.
+> Deliverable: `npm test` runs ≥ 12 unit tests covering move, push, win, undo, history, all passing. Zero DOM imports in `core/`.
+
+## Locked Decisions
+
+### D1: Module layout
+- **Decision**: Pure functions in `src/core/`: `reducer.ts`, `move.ts`, `winCheck.ts`, `history.ts`. No imports from `render/`, `input/`, `anim/`, `dom`, `storage`. Importable in Vitest with zero DOM setup.
+- **Rationale**: Matches architecture research Section "Module Boundaries (no god-objects)"; `core/` is the simulation layer where every acceptance-critical rule (move validity, push, win, undo) lives.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Single `game.ts` god-object (rejected — untestable without DOM/canvas).
+- **Impact**: All `core/` files; tests live in `tests/unit/core/`.
+
+### D2: Types — extend `src/types.ts`
+- **Decision**: Add `GameState`, `HistoryEntry`, `AnimSpec`, `Level` to `src/types.ts`. Keep `Direction`, `Coord`, `Tile`, `Intent` from ph.1.
+- **Rationale**: All cross-module types live in one place per architecture; reducer consumes `Intent`, returns `GameState` + optional `AnimSpec`.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Per-module type files (rejected — types are referenced across modules).
+- **Impact**: `src/types.ts` will be ~80 lines by end of ph.2.
+
+### D3: GameState shape (immutable)
+- **Decision**: `GameState` is immutable; each reducer call returns a new object with shallow-copied `boxes`/`history`; `static` is reused by reference.
+- **Rationale**: Architecture research "State Model (immutable GameState)" — undo is replay/snapshot-stack friendly; pure functions testable.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Mutable state with manual cloning (rejected — error-prone).
+- **Impact**: All core functions; ph.3+ shell consumes `GameState`.
+
+### D4: Win check algorithm
+- **Decision**: `O(B)` — `boxes.length === targets.size && boxes.every(b => targets.has(b))`. Recomputed inside reducer on move, undo, AND reset (not only on move).
+- **Rationale**: Architecture research "Win-check algorithm" — single source of truth; cheap at ≤30 boxes.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Incremental counter on push (rejected — adds state for no gain at this scale).
+- **Impact**: `winCheck.ts`; reducer invokes on every transition.
+
+### D5: Undo stack representation (entry-based, unlimited depth)
+- **Decision**: `HistoryEntry = { player, pushedBoxIndex?, boxFrom?, moveCount }`. Push entry on every successful move; pop on undo. No depth cap.
+- **Rationale**: Architecture research "Undo stack representation" — entry-based is O(1) memory per move vs O(level-size) snapshots; unlimited per NFR-6.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Full-state snapshots per move (rejected — entry-based exposes push semantics directly for tests).
+- **Impact**: `history.ts`; reducer pushes on move, pops on undo.
+
+### D6: Reset semantics — clear undo stack
+- **Decision**: `reset` clears the undo stack (reset = fresh start boundary). User cannot undo into pre-reset history.
+- **Rationale**: Matches player intuition; simpler than preserving stack; documented in tests.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Preserve stack (undo returns to pre-reset state) — rejected, surprising behavior.
+- **Impact**: reducer `reset` branch; `tests/unit/core/reducer.test.ts` covers this explicitly.
+
+### D7: Invalid move handling — return same state
+- **Decision**: When `move` is invalid (wall / blocked box), reducer returns the same logical state object (same reference), no anim spec.
+- **Rationale**: No allocation on invalid moves; caller can `===` check to detect "no change"; pure-function semantics preserved.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Return `null` (rejected — forces every caller to null-check; less ergonomic).
+- **Impact**: `move.ts` returns either new `Coord` or unchanged; reducer passes through.
+
+### D8: AnimSpec shape — defined now, unused until ph.5
+- **Decision**: `AnimSpec = { from, to, duration, entities: ('player' | number)[] }` defined in `src/types.ts` from this phase. Reducer emits `anim?: AnimSpec` on every successful move; **omits** `anim` on undo/reset (snap-only in ph.2; ph.5 may add reverse tween for undo as an optional refinement).
+- **Rationale**: Define the interface now so ph.5 plugs in without reducer signature change. Undo as snap is simpler and matches the architecture's "no queue blocking" NFR.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Defer AnimSpec to ph.5 (rejected — requires reducer signature change in ph.5, more churn).
+- **Impact**: Reducer signature `{ state, anim? }`; ph.5's animator consumes `AnimSpec` directly.
+
+### D9: Box identity — index-based
+- **Decision**: Boxes are an array of `Coord`; index = box identity. Pushing box at index `i` updates `boxes[i]`.
+- **Rationale**: Architecture research "State Model" — order-stable array; index is the natural identity for ≤10 boxes.
+- **Alternatives considered**: `Map<id, Coord>` (rejected — adds Map overhead; IDs would need to be strings which are less ergonomic).
+- **Impact**: All reducer branches operate on `boxes[i]`.
+
+### D10: Test framework conventions
+- **Decision**: All `core/` tests live under `tests/unit/core/` and run under the `unit` project (node env — pure logic). Use Vitest's `describe` / `it` / `expect`. Each test sets up a level inline (no shared fixtures yet — ph.3 introduces the loader).
+- **Rationale**: Fast node env; explicit fixtures per test for clarity; ph.3's loader will give us real levels to test against.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Fixture files per test (rejected — overkill for pure logic).
+- **Impact**: All ph.2 tests.
+
+## Gray Areas (Unresolved)
+
+None. All decisions clear from `bp/requirements.md`, `bp/research/architecture.md` (Section: State Model, Undo Stack Representation, Win-check Algorithm, Animation Interruption), `bp/research/pitfalls.md` BLOCKER #3, #4, MAJOR #17, and ph.1-foundation artifacts. Express path taken per user direction.
+
+## Deferred Ideas
+
+- **Deadlock detection** — `ph.8-e2e-and-deadlock` adds the corner-trap check. Not in ph.2 because the basic game logic is the priority; deadlock is a polish feature.
+- **Animator / tween** — ph.5 introduces `src/anim/animator.ts`. ph.2 reducer emits `AnimSpec` data values but no animator consumes them yet.
+- **Level loader / validator** — ph.3.
+- **Renderer / keyboard input / gameShell** — ph.3.
+- **Touch / responsive / persistence** — ph.6, ph.7.
+
+## Non-Goals
+
+- Not implementing the renderer (ph.3).
+- Not implementing keyboard input (ph.3).
+- Not implementing the game shell orchestrator (ph.3).
+- Not loading levels from JSON (ph.3).
+- Not implementing the rAF animator (ph.5).
+- Not implementing touch input (ph.6).
+- Not implementing localStorage persistence (ph.7).
+- Not implementing deadlock detection (ph.8).
+- Not adding linting or commit hooks (ph.9).
+- Not adding e2e tests (ph.8).
+- Not deploying to GitHub Pages (ph.9).
